  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya Emergency Drought Response &#x2013; Food, NFIs and WATSAN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Distribution of food vouchers, NFIs, hygiene kits, water trucking, repair of five boreholes, Improved access to primary health care facilities and sanitation, Hygiene awareness and carcass disposal, Support women groups with sanitation hand tools, Provision of aqua tabs and construction of pit latrines</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Elderly, Pastoralists, Agro-Pastoralists</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide emergency relief to older people and their families in pastoralist communities through the provision of food, non-food items and water trucking. In addition it will also support community-led early recovery activities through the rehabilitation of borehole and construction of household latrines and provision of water purification by distributing aqua tabs to improve sanitation and access to safe and clean water in drought affected areas of North Eastern Kenya.</narrative>
  </description>
